item.title: Nord: Character (creature) design
item.media:title: Nord: Character (creature) design
item.media:description:
Alright so as the exam I made these for is passed I want to show you how The Ideal Right Work Process is expected to be starting from this one fav.me/dcxl8n4 than there goes  fav.me/dcxq1ej  fav.me/dcxz13z and fav.me/dcy0h5r

And here's the result

I meant these to be the creatures living in my in-game story. The Sun and The Moon are going through the world that just starts to be made. They move from the most like finished area of The Woods to the location of The Dark where it all started. So their temple is located in The Woods. There is also the people village if you move forward a little bit. Than there is Water location and Stone location after them, and further everithing is in The Dark.

item.media:title: Infernape Used Flare Blitz
item.media:description:
Infernape using flare blitz for Pokemon gen4 tribute project.

Gen 4 is my favorite, so I chose to claim three favorites from the many I have, hehe. Here, infernape.

About the project:  The Pokemon Gen IV Tribute starts right now!
Surprise, surprise
Since I myself, and also shinragod Hedgey and freqrexy are currently working on the last galleries for our Pokemon Gen III Tribute I thought it can not hurt to start with the Pokemon Gen IV Project already slowly and only for you, the GA-HQ Contributors who participated in previous art collaborations.
Examples from our Gen III Tribute:

You can see the progress of our Gen III Tribute here btw: http://www.game-art-hq.com/128460/the-game-art-hq-community-presents-the-pokemon-generation-iii-art-collaboration/
Since Friday, I am finetuning/finishing 1-3 of the 170 galleries and am sharing one gallery per day currently via the @gamearthq Twitter account.
You are welcome to follow it of course. It's also useful if you can share your own Twitter accounts so I can tag and link you all in the Tweets.
I am going to create a new "main hub" for the Pokemon Tribute galleries THIS WEEK on Game

item.title: Gilded Eeveelutions Series: Sylveon
item.media:title: Gilded Eeveelutions Series: Sylveon
item.media:description:
Gilded Eeveelutions Series: A collection of works that features the harmony of black and gold!


My second favourite Eeveelution, but definitely the cutest (*´ ω `)

The last piece of this series! I had a lot of fun with this, especially getting to try the Pilot Super Color Gold Pen for the first time for that delicious metallic shine. It's pretty difficult to work with, but you can't deny that it's probably one of the best metallic pens I've used in a while! I'll have to try some other gold markers for comparison purposes sometime though c:

Prints of this are available on my Etsy!


Strathmore 400 Series Smooth Bristol
Pigma Micron Pen

item.title: - World Gaze -
item.media:title: - World Gaze -
item.media:description:
"...The world carves into shape based on the consequences of today.

    Where will you lead it to?"



Press "spacebar" to toggle its appearance.

Another pixel project! Initially, it was meant to function in a way that the appearance of this animation changes based on your device's time that you're viewing it, but because my flash ran into technical problems and bugs from doing so, that was a little disheartening to me.
On the bright side, taking this alternate way would let you view these three appearances in one go: twilight, night and day.

Back at it again with cityscapes, haha.

Music credit: "Blueshift" by LawnReality. Check 'em out!
Starla | Elanolia © StR-Lite.
